Sentencas: High oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity and sufficient stability are main challenges for high performance cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) operated at medium temperature (550-700 degrees C).
Titulo: High-performance and CO2-resistant cathode toward electrocatalytic oxygen reduction for solid oxide fuel cells: Doped ceria and SrCo0.7Nb0.1Ni0.2O3-δ composite

Sentencas: In this study, ionic conducting Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta (SDC) are incorporated into perovskite SrCo0.7Nb0.1Ni0.2O3-delta (SCNN) cathode to synergistically improve its ORR activity as well as CO2 tolerance.
Titulo: High-performance and CO2-resistant cathode toward electrocatalytic oxygen reduction for solid oxide fuel cells: Doped ceria and SrCo0.7Nb0.1Ni0.2O3-δ composite

Sentencas: A series of composite oxide, SCNN-xSDC (x = 0, 20, 30, 40 and 50 wt %), were systematically evaluated as candidate cathodes for intermediate temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: High-performance and CO2-resistant cathode toward electrocatalytic oxygen reduction for solid oxide fuel cells: Doped ceria and SrCo0.7Nb0.1Ni0.2O3-δ composite

Sentencas: Among all cathodes, SCNN-40SDC has the lowest polarization resistance (0.019 Omega(2) cm(2)), only similar to 30% of SCNN (0.066 Omega(2) cm(2)) at 700 degrees C. Introduction appropriate
Titulo: High-performance and CO2-resistant cathode toward electrocatalytic oxygen reduction for solid oxide fuel cells: Doped ceria and SrCo0.7Nb0.1Ni0.2O3-δ composite

Sentencas: SDC boosts ORR activity of the composite cathodes, which is owing to enhanced oxygen surface exchange process, as evidenced by higher oxygen surface exchange coefficient (K-chem) and bulk diffusion coefficient (D-chem).
Titulo: High-performance and CO2-resistant cathode toward electrocatalytic oxygen reduction for solid oxide fuel cells: Doped ceria and SrCo0.7Nb0.1Ni0.2O3-δ composite

Sentencas: Furthermore, the composite cathode shows much enhanced stability under CO2 poisoning, which was ascribed to the suppression of Sr segregation from SrCo0.7Nb0.1Ni0.2O3-delta and alleviated formation of carbonate in condition of SDC addition.
Titulo: High-performance and CO2-resistant cathode toward electrocatalytic oxygen reduction for solid oxide fuel cells: Doped ceria and SrCo0.7Nb0.1Ni0.2O3-δ composite

Sentencas: Introducing ionic conductor Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta to construct a dual-phase cathode is a promising way to improve stability and ORR activity of perovskite oxides for SOFCs.
Titulo: High-performance and CO2-resistant cathode toward electrocatalytic oxygen reduction for solid oxide fuel cells: Doped ceria and SrCo0.7Nb0.1Ni0.2O3-δ composite
